# Architecture Rules

## Sources of Truth
- [[ARCHITECTURE]] is canonical for environment topology.
- Domain overviews specialize; they must not contradict the brain file.

## Diagrams
- Prefer Mermaid for topology, trust boundaries, and data flows.
- One diagram answers one question.
- Keep VLAN/subnet values accurate or mark as placeholders with TODOs.

## Inventories
- Use tables for hosts/services.
- Include role, zone, platform, status, last-verified when known.

## Change Management
- Topology changes update [[ARCHITECTURE]] and affected overviews in the same change set.
- Record significant decisions with Decision Record template.
